statement:
Find all polynomials \( P \) in two variables with:
\begin{enumerate}
\item[(i)] \( P(tx,ty)=t^{n}P(x,y) \) for some positive integer \( n \) and all real \( t,x,y \) (homogeneous of degree \( n \));
\item[(ii)] \( P(b+c,a)+P(c+a,b)+P(a+b,c)=0 \) for all real \( a,b,c \);
\item[(iii)] \( P(x,0)=1 \).
\end{enumerate}
